This paper is primarily focused on analyzing performance variability in datacenter environments, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses statistical methods such as changepoint detection to analyze the data, which could fall under Probability (cs.PF) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of workload policies on performance, which could fall under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) or Architecture (cs.AR).
